LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

EstimatedTravelTime.title: Estimated Travel Time (Minutes)
EstimatedTravelTime.description: The estimated number of minutes needed for the service resource to travel to the service appointment they’re assigned to. You can enter a value with up to two decimal places.

ActualTravelTime.title: Actual Travel Time (Minutes)
ActualTravelTime.description: The number of minutes that the service resource needs to travel to the assigned service appointment. You can enter a value with up to two decimal places.

IsPrimaryResource.title: Primary Resource
IsPrimaryResource.description: Indicates whether the service resource is a primary resource or not. The default value is false. Available in API version 47.0 and later.

LocationStatus.title: Location Status
LocationStatus.description: The status of the mobile worker approaching the service appointment. When the location status changes to one of these values, a status update containing ApptAssistantInfoUrl is sent to the customer. Available in version 51.0 and later.

ApptAssistantInfoUrl.title: Appointment Assistant Info Url
ApptAssistantInfoUrl.description: The URL that contains the status of the mobile worker approaching the service appointment, the Community URL, and the expiry of the URL. Available in version 51.0 and later.

schema.description: [Field Service Lightning] Represents a service technician or service crew in Field Service and Salesforce Scheduler, or an agent in Workforce Engagement.

Id.title: Resource ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Name
Name.description: The resource’s name, for example the name or title of the associated user or service crew.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

ResourceType.title: Resource Type
ResourceType.description: Indicates whether the resource is a Technician (T), Dispatcher (D), Crew (C), Asset (S), Agent (A), or Planner (P). The default value is Technician (T). Resources who are dispatchers can’t be capacity-based or included in scheduling optimization. Only users with the Field Service Dispatcher permission-set license can be dispatchers. You can’t add additional resource types. To create a dependent lookup filter with ServiceResource.ResourceType, use only the first letter of the picklist value, for example T for Technician.

IsActive.title: Active
IsActive.description: When selected, this option means that the resource can be assigned to work orders. For service tracking purposes, resources can’t be deleted, so deactivating a resource is the best way to send them into retirement.Deactivating a user doesn’t deactivate the related service resource. You can’t create a service resource that is linked to an inactive user.

IsCapacityBased.title: Capacity-Based
IsCapacityBased.description: Capacity-based resources are limited to a certain number of hours or appointments in a specified time period. Tip The Capacities related list shows a resource’s capacity.

IsOptimizationCapable.title: Include in Scheduling Optimization
IsOptimizationCapable.description: This field is reserved for Field Service and the managed package. Create a custom field instead of using this field to include a service resource in optimization.

LastKnownLatitude.title: Last Known Latitude
LastKnownLatitude.description: The service resource’s last known location. You can configure this field to display data collected from a custom mobile app. This field isn’t visible in the user interface, but you can expose it on service resource page layouts or set up field tracking to be able to view a resource’s location history.

LastKnownLongitude.title: Last Known Longitude
LastKnownLongitude.description: The service resource’s last known location. You can configure this field to display data collected from a custom mobile app. This field isn’t visible in the user interface, but you can expose it on service resource page layouts or set up field tracking to be able to view a resource’s location history.

LastKnownLocation.title: Last Known Location
LastKnownLocation.description: The service resource’s last known location. You can configure this field to display data collected from a custom mobile app. This field isn’t visible in the user interface, but you can expose it on service resource page layouts or set up field tracking to be able to view a resource’s location history.

LastKnownLocationDate.title: Last Known Location Date
LastKnownLocationDate.description: The date and time of the last known location.

schema.description: [Field Service Lightning] Represents an appointment to complete work for a customer in Field Service, Lightning Scheduler,Intelligent Appointment Management, and Virtual Care.

Id.title: Service Appointment ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

ParentRecordType.title: Parent Record Type
ParentRecordType.description: (Read only) The type of parent record: Account, Asset, Lead, Opportunity, Work Order, or Work Order Line Item.

Street.title: Street
Street.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

City.title: City
City.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

State.title: State/Province
State.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

PostalCode.title: Zip/Postal Code
PostalCode.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

Country.title: Country
Country.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

Latitude.title: Latitude
Latitude.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

Longitude.title: Longitude
Longitude.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

GeocodeAccuracy.title: Geocode Accuracy
GeocodeAccuracy.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

Address.title: Address
Address.description: The address where the appointment is taking place. The address is inherited from the parent record if the parent record is a work order or work order line item.

EarliestStartTime.title: Earliest Start Permitted
EarliestStartTime.description: The date after which the appointment must be completed. Earliest Start Permitted and Due Date typically reflect terms in the customer’s service-level agreement.

DueDate.title: Due Date
DueDate.description: The date by which the appointment must be completed. Earliest Start Permitted and Due Date typically reflect terms in the customer’s service-level agreement.

Duration.title: Duration
Duration.description: The estimated length of the appointment. If the parent record is work order or work order line item, the appointment inherits its parent’s duration, but it can be manually updated. The duration is in minutes or hours based on the value selected in the Duration Type field.

ArrivalWindowStartTime.title: Arrival Window Start
ArrivalWindowStartTime.description: The beginning of the window of time in which the technician is scheduled to arrive at the site. This window is typically larger than the Scheduled Start and End window to allow time for delays and scheduling changes. You may choose to share the Arrival Window Start and End with the customer, but keep the Scheduled Start and End internal-only.

ArrivalWindowEndTime.title: Arrival Window End
ArrivalWindowEndTime.description: The end of the window of time in which the technician is scheduled to arrive at the site. This window is typically larger than the Scheduled Start and End window to allow time for delays and scheduling changes. You may choose to share the Arrival Window Start and End with the customer, but keep the Scheduled Start and End internal-only.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: The status of the appointment. The picklist includes the following values, which can be customized: None—Default value. Scheduled—Appointment has been assigned to a service resource. Dispatched—Assigned service resource has been notified about their assignment. In Progress—Work has begun. Completed—Work is complete. Cannot Complete—Work could not be completed. Canceled—Work is canceled, typically before any work began

SchedStartTime.title: Scheduled Start
SchedStartTime.description: The time at which the appointment is scheduled to start. If you are using the Field Service managed package with the scheduling optimizer, this field is populated once the appointment is assigned to a resource.

SchedEndTime.title: Scheduled End
SchedEndTime.description: The time at which the appointment is scheduled to end. If you are using the Field Service managed package with the scheduling optimizer, this field is populated once the appointment is assigned to a resource. Scheduled End – Scheduled Start = Estimated Duration.

ActualStartTime.title: Actual Start
ActualStartTime.description: The actual date and time the appointment started.

ActualEndTime.title: Actual End
ActualEndTime.description: The actual date and time the appointment ended.

ActualDuration.title: Actual Duration (Minutes)
ActualDuration.description: The number of minutes that it took the resource to complete the appointment after arriving at the address. When values are first added to the Actual Start and Actual End fields, the Actual Duration is automatically populated to list the difference between the Actual Start and Actual End. If the Actual Start and Actual End fields are subsequently updated, the Actual Duration field doesn’t re-update, but you can manually update it.

DurationType.title: Duration Type
DurationType.description: The unit of the Duration: Minutes or Hours.

Subject.title: Subject
Subject.description: A short phrase describing the appointment.

ParentRecordStatusCategory.title: Parent Record Status Category
ParentRecordStatusCategory.description: (Read only) The Status Category of the parent record. If the parent record is a work order or work order line item, this field is populated; otherwise, it remains blank.

StatusCategory.title: Status Category
StatusCategory.description: The category that each Status value falls into. The Status Category field’s values are identical to the default Status values.If you create custom Status values, you must indicate which category it belongs to. For example, if you create a Customer Absent value, you may decide that it belongs in the Cannot Complete category. To learn which processes reference StatusCategory, see How are Status Categories Used?

IsAnonymousBooking.title: Anonymous Booking
IsAnonymousBooking.description: Indicates whether a service resource was automatically assigned to the appointment. The default value is false.

IsManuallyBundled.title: Manually Bundled
IsManuallyBundled.description: Indicates if this bundle was created manually. The default value is false.

IsBundleMember.title: Bundle Member
IsBundleMember.description: Indicates if this service appointment is a bundle member service appointment. The default value is false.

IsBundle.title: Bundle
IsBundle.description: Indicates if this service appointment is a bundle service appointment. The default value is false.

IsOffsiteAppointment.title: Offsite Appointment
IsOffsiteAppointment.description: Any type of work that can be done remotely.

ServiceDocumentTemplate.title: Service Document Template
ServiceDocumentTemplate.description: The template ID which sets the template for each service document for the Document Builder feature.

Id.title: Order ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

EffectiveDate.title: Order Start Date
EffectiveDate.description: Date at which the order becomes effective. Label is Order Start Date.

EndDate.title: Order End Date
EndDate.description: Date at which the order ends. Label is Order End Date.

IsReductionOrder.title: Reduction Order
IsReductionOrder.description: Read-only. Determines whether an order is a reduction order. Label is Reduction Order.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: Picklist of values that indicate order status. Each value is within one of two status categories defined in StatusCode. For example, the status picklist might contain Draft, Ready for Review, and Ready for Activation values with a StatusCode of Draft.

CustomerAuthorizedDate.title: Customer Authorized Date
CustomerAuthorizedDate.description: Date on which the contact authorized the order.

CompanyAuthorizedDate.title: Company Authorized Date
CompanyAuthorizedDate.description: The date on which your organization authorized the order.

Type.title: Order Type
Type.description: If you want to show more information about your order, you can add custom values to the Type picklist. By default, the Type field doesn't perform any actions or show any values.

PoNumber.title: PO Number
PoNumber.description: Number identifying the purchase order. Maximum is 80.

OrderReferenceNumber.title: Order Reference Number
OrderReferenceNumber.description: Order reference number assigned to this order. Maximum size is 80 characters.

ActivatedDate.title: Activated Date
ActivatedDate.description: Date and time when the order was activated.

StatusCode.title: Status Category
StatusCode.description: The status category for the order. An order can be either Draft or Activated. Label is Status Category.

TaxLocaleType.title: Tax Locale Type
TaxLocaleType.description: The type of tax calculation that Salesforce uses for the order’s order items. VAT regions use gross tax, which includes tax in all sale amounts. US regions use net tax, which calculates tax separately from the initial sale amount and then adds the sale and tax amounts together in a total.

OrderedDate.title: Ordered Date
OrderedDate.description: The date and time that the order was placed.

BillingEmailAddress.title: Billing Email Address
BillingEmailAddress.description: Email address for this order’s billing address.

BillingPhoneNumber.title: Billing Phone Number
BillingPhoneNumber.description: Phone number for this order’s billing address.

OrderManagementReferenceIdentifier.title: Order Management Reference Identifier
OrderManagementReferenceIdentifier.description: This field is used by Order Management to store the external reference Identifier for B2C Commerce orders. On creation, the B2C Integration sets this value to B2C realm ID + "_"+ B2C instance ID + "@"+ B2C Commerce catalog/domain ID + "@"+ B2C Commerce order number. Otherwise, it isn’t set.

OrderNumber.title: Order Number
OrderNumber.description: Order number assigned to this order (not the unique, system-generated ID assigned during creation). Maximum size is 30 characters.

TotalAmount.title: Order Amount
TotalAmount.description: The net total amount for the order products associated with this order.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

TypicalInTerritoryTravelTime.title: Typical In-Territory Travel Time (Minutes)
TypicalInTerritoryTravelTime.description: Estimated number of minutes needed to travel from one location to another within the service territory. You can use this field in Apex customization.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: The picklist of values that indicate order status. Each value is within one of two status categories defined in StatusCode. For example, the status picklist may contain: Ready to Ship, Shipped, Received as values within the Activated StatusCode.

CompanySignedDate.title: Company Signed Date

CustomerSignedTitle.title: Customer Signed Title

SpecialTerms.title: Special Terms

ActivatedDate.title: Activated Date

StatusCode.title: Status Category
StatusCode.description: The status category for the contract. A contract can be Draft, InApproval, or Activated. Label is Status Category.

LastApprovedDate.title: Last Approved Date
LastApprovedDate.description: Last date the contract was approved.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LastActivityDate.title: Last Activity

schema.description: [Field Service Lightning] Represents a subtask on a work order in field service.

Id.title: Work Order Line Item ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

CurrencyIsoCode.title: Currency ISO Code
CurrencyIsoCode.description: Available only for orgs with the multicurrency feature enabled. Contains the ISO code for any currency allowed by the organization. The label in the user interface is Currency ISO Code.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

ParentWorkOrderLineItemId.title: Parent Work Order Line Item ID

RootWorkOrderLineItemId.title: Root Work Order Line Item ID

Description.title: Description
Description.description: The description of the work order line item. Try to describe the steps needed to mark the line item Completed.

StartDate.title: Start Date
StartDate.description: The date on which the line item goes into effect. This field is blank unless you set up an Apex trigger or quick action to populate it. For example, you can create a quick action that sets the StartDate to the date when the Status changes to In Progress.

EndDate.title: End Date
EndDate.description: The date on which the line item is completed. This field is blank unless you set up an Apex trigger or quick action to populate it. For example, you can create a quick action that sets the EndDate to 365 days after the StartDate.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: The status of the line item. The picklist includes the following values, which can be customized: New—Line item was created, but there hasn’t yet been any activity. In Progress—Work has begun. On Hold—Work is paused. Completed—Work is complete. Cannot Complete—Work could not be completed. Closed—All work and associated activity is complete. Canceled—Work is canceled, typically before any work began.

Quantity.title: Quantity
Quantity.description: Number of units of the line item included in the associated work order.

UnitPrice.title: Unit Price
UnitPrice.description: Initially, the unit price for a work order line item is the line item’s list price from the price book, but you can change it.

Discount.title: Discount
Discount.description: The percent discount to apply to the line item. You can enter a number with or without the percent symbol, and you can use up to two decimal places.

ListPrice.title: List Price
ListPrice.description: The price of the line item (product) as listed in its corresponding price book entry. If a price book entry isn’t specified, the list price defaults to zero.

Subtotal.title: Subtotal
Subtotal.description: (Read only) The line item’s unit price multiplied by the quantity.

TotalPrice.title: Total Price
TotalPrice.description: Read only. The line item’s subtotal with discounts applied.

Duration.title: Duration
Duration.description: The estimated time required to complete the line item. Specify the duration unit in the Duration Type field. Note Work order duration and work order line item duration are independent of each other. If you want work order duration to automatically show the sum of the work order line items’ duration, replace the Duration field on work orders with a custom roll-up summary field.

DurationType.title: Duration Type
DurationType.description: The unit of the duration: Minutes or Hours.

DurationInMinutes.title: Duration in Minutes
DurationInMinutes.description: The estimated duration in minutes. For internal use only.

Street.title: Street
Street.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

City.title: City
City.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

State.title: State/Province
State.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

PostalCode.title: Zip/Postal Code
PostalCode.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

Country.title: Country
Country.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

Latitude.title: Latitude
Latitude.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

Longitude.title: Longitude
Longitude.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

GeocodeAccuracy.title: Geocode Accuracy
GeocodeAccuracy.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

Address.title: Address
Address.description: The compound form of the address where the line item is completed.

Subject.title: Subject
Subject.description: A word or phrase describing the line item.

StatusCategory.title: Status Category
StatusCategory.description: The category that each Status value falls into. The Status Category field has eight default values: seven values which are identical to the default Status values, and a None value for statuses without a status category.If you create custom Status values, you must indicate which category it belongs to. For example, if you create a Waiting for Response value, you may decide that it belongs in the On Hold category. To learn which processes reference StatusCategory, see How are Status Categories Used?

IsClosed.title: Is Closed
IsClosed.description: Indicates whether the line item has been closed. Changing the line item’s status to Closed causes this checkbox to be selected in the user interface (sets IsClosed to true). Tip Use this field to report on closed versus open work order line items.

Priority.title: Priority
Priority.description: The priority of the line item. The picklist includes the following values, which can be customized: Low Medium High Critical

ServiceAppointmentCount.title: Service Appointment Count
ServiceAppointmentCount.description: The number of service appointments on the work order line item.

MinimumCrewSize.title: Minimum Crew Size
MinimumCrewSize.description: The minimum crew size allowed for a crew assigned to the line item. If you’re not using the Field Service managed package, this field serves as a suggestion rather than a rule. If you are using the managed package, the scheduling optimizer counts the number of service crew members on a service crew to determine whether it fits a work order line item’s minimum crew size requirement.

RecommendedCrewSize.title: Recommended Crew Size
RecommendedCrewSize.description: The recommended number of people on the service crew assigned to the line item. For example, you might have a Minimum Crew Size of 2 and a Recommended Crew Size of 3.

SuggestedMaintenanceDate.title: Suggested Maintenance Date
SuggestedMaintenanceDate.description: Date when maintenance work is planned.

IsGeneratedFromMaintenancePlan.title: Generated from maintenance plan
IsGeneratedFromMaintenancePlan.description: Identifies whether the work order line item is generated from a maintenance plan.

ServiceDocumentTemplate.title: Service Document Template
ServiceDocumentTemplate.description: The template ID which sets the template for each service document for the Document Builder feature.

data.label: Work Order Line Item

schema.description: [Core] Represents a warehouse, service vehicle, work site, or other element of the region where your team performs field service work. In API version 49.0 and later, you can associate activities with specific locations. Activities, such as the tasks and events related to a location, appear in the activities timeline when you view the location detail page. Also in API version 49.0 and later, Work.com users can view Employees as a related list on Location records. In API version 51.0 and later, this object is available for Omnichannel Inventory and represents physical locations where inventory is available for fulfilling orders.

Id.title: Location ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

Name.title: Location Name
Name.description: The name of the location. For example, Service Van #4.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

LocationType.title: Location Type
LocationType.description: Picklist of location types. It has no default values, so you must populate it before creating any location records.

Description.title: Description
Description.description: A brief description of the location.

PossessionDate.title: Possession Date
PossessionDate.description: The date the location was purchased.

ConstructionStartDate.title: Construction Start Date
ConstructionStartDate.description: Date construction began at the location.

ConstructionEndDate.title: Construction End Date
ConstructionEndDate.description: Date construction ended at the location.

OpenDate.title: Open Date
OpenDate.description: Date the location opened or came into service.

CloseDate.title: Close Date
CloseDate.description: Date the location closed or went out of service.

RemodelStartDate.title: Remodel Start Date
RemodelStartDate.description: Date when remodel construction started at the location.

RemodelEndDate.title: Remodel End Date
RemodelEndDate.description: Date when remodel construction ended at the location.

IsMobile.title: Mobile Location
IsMobile.description: Indicates whether the location moves. For example, a truck or tool box.

IsInventoryLocation.title: Inventory Location
IsInventoryLocation.description: Indicates whether the location stores parts. Note This field must be selected if you want to associate the location with product items.

LocationLevel.title: Location Level
LocationLevel.description: The location’s position in a location hierarchy. If the location has no parent or child locations, its level is 1. Locations that belong to a hierarchy have a level of 1 for the root location, 2 for the child locations of the root location, 3 for their children, and so forth.

ShouldSyncWithOci.title: Sync with OCI
ShouldSyncWithOci.description: Indicates whether the location should sync its data with Omnichannel Inventory. The default value is false.

Priority.title: Priority
Priority.description: The priority of the location when routing orders. No default values are included. Add values to the picklist and reference them in your custom routing logic.

FoCapacity.title: Fulfillment Order Capacity
FoCapacity.description: The maximum number of fulfillment orders that can be assigned to the location per time period. If this value is null, then this location’s capacity isn’t limited.

AssignedFoCount.title: Assigned Fulfillment Order Count
AssignedFoCount.description: The number of fulfillment orders assigned to the location. Confirming held fulfillment order capacity increments this value. To reset the location’s capacity, set this value to 0.

ShouldTrackFoCapacity.title: Track Fulfillment Order Capacity
ShouldTrackFoCapacity.description: Indicates whether the location should track its fulfillment order capacity. The default value is false.

data.description: [Core] Represents a warehouse, service vehicle, work site, or other element of the region where your team performs field service work. In API version 49.0 and later, you can associate activities with specific locations. Activities, such as the tasks and events related to a location, appear in the activities timeline when you view the location detail page. Also in API version 49.0 and later, Work.com users can view Employees as a related list on Location records. In API version 51.0 and later, this object is available for Omnichannel Inventory and represents physical locations where inventory is available for fulfilling orders.
data.label: Location

Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

Type.title: Type
Type.description: The type of entitlement, such as Web or phone support.

StartDate.title: Start Date
StartDate.description: The first date the entitlement is in effect.

EndDate.title: End Date
EndDate.description: The last day the entitlement is in effect.

IsPerIncident.title: Per Incident
IsPerIncident.description: Indicates whether the entitlement is limited to supporting a specific number of cases (true) or not (false).

CasesPerEntitlement.title: Cases Per Entitlement
CasesPerEntitlement.description: The total number of cases the entitlement supports.

RemainingCases.title: Remaining Cases
RemainingCases.description: The number of cases the entitlement can support. This field decreases in value by one each time a case is created with the entitlement.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: Status of the entitlement, such as Expired.

SvcApptBookingWindowsId.title: Operating Hour ID
SvcApptBookingWindowsId.description: The operating hours of the entitlement. This field is visible only if Field Service is enabled.

WorkOrdersPerEntitlement.title: Work Orders Per Entitlement
WorkOrdersPerEntitlement.description: Total number of work orders available for this entitlement.

RemainingWorkOrders.title: Remaining Work Orders
RemainingWorkOrders.description: The number of agreed work orders remaining to be created.

Id.title: Work Order ID
Id.description: Globally unique string that identifies a record.

CurrencyIsoCode.title: Currency ISO Code
CurrencyIsoCode.description: Available only for orgs with the multicurrency feature enabled. Contains the ISO code for any currency allowed by the organization. The label in the user interface is Currency ISO Code.

LastModifiedDate.title: Last Modified Date
LastModifiedDate.description: Date and time when a user last modified this record.

Street.title: Street
Street.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

City.title: City
City.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

State.title: State/Province
State.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

PostalCode.title: Zip/Postal Code
PostalCode.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

Country.title: Country
Country.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

Latitude.title: Latitude
Latitude.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

Longitude.title: Longitude
Longitude.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

GeocodeAccuracy.title: Geocode Accuracy
GeocodeAccuracy.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

Address.title: Address
Address.description: The compound form of the address where the work order is completed.

Description.title: Description
Description.description: The description of the work order. Try to include the steps needed to change the work order’s status to Completed.

StartDate.title: Start Date
StartDate.description: The date when the work order goes into effect. This field is blank unless you set up an Apex trigger or quick action to populate it. For example, you can create a quick action that sets the StartDate to the date when the Status changes to In Progress.

EndDate.title: End Date
EndDate.description: The date when the work order is completed. This field is blank unless you set up an Apex trigger or quick action to populate it. For example, you can create a quick action that sets the EndDate to 365 days after the StartDate.

Subject.title: Subject
Subject.description: The subject of the work order. Try to describe the nature and purpose of the job to be completed. For example, “Annual On-Site Well Maintenance.” Maximum length is 255 characters.

Status.title: Status
Status.description: The status of the work order. The picklist includes the following values, which can be customized: New—Work order was created, but there hasn’t yet been any activity. In Progress—Work has begun. On Hold—Work is paused. Completed—Work is complete. Cannot Complete—Work could not be completed. Closed—All work and associated activity is complete. Canceled—Work is canceled, typically before any work began. Changing a work order’s status does not affect the status of its work order line items or associated service appointments.

Priority.title: Priority
Priority.description: The priority of the work order. The picklist includes the following values, which can be customized: Low Medium High Critical

Tax.title: Tax
Tax.description: The total tax on the work order. You can enter a number with or without the currency symbol and use up to two decimal places. For example, in a work order whose total price is $100, enter $10 to apply a 10% tax.

Subtotal.title: Subtotal
Subtotal.description: Read only. The total of the work order line items’ subtotals before discounts and taxes are applied.

TotalPrice.title: Total Price
TotalPrice.description: Read only. The total of the work order line items’ prices. This value has discounts applied but not tax.

LineItemCount.title: Line Items
LineItemCount.description: The number of work order line items in the work order. Its label in the user interface is Line Items.

Discount.title: Discount
Discount.description: Read only. The weighted average of the discounts on all line items in the work order. It can be any positive number up to 100.

GrandTotal.title: Grand Total
GrandTotal.description: Read only. The total price of the work order with tax added.

IsClosed.title: Is Closed
IsClosed.description: Indicates whether the work order is closed (true) or open (false). Tip Use this field to report on closed versus open work orders.

IsStopped.title: Stopped
IsStopped.description: Indicates whether a milestone is paused (true) or counting down (false). This field is available only if Enable stopped time and actual elapsed time is selected on the Entitlement Settings page.

StopStartDate.title: Stopped Since
StopStartDate.description: Indicates when the milestone was paused. The label in the user interface is Stopped Since.

SlaStartDate.title: Sla Policy Start Time
SlaStartDate.description: The time that the work order enters the entitlement process. You can update or reset the time if you have “Edit” permission on work orders.

SlaExitDate.title: Sla Policy End Time
SlaExitDate.description: The time that the work order exits the entitlement process.

MilestoneStatus.title: Milestone Status
MilestoneStatus.description: Indicates the status of a milestone. This field is visible if an entitlement process is applied to a work order.

Duration.title: Duration
Duration.description: The estimated time required to complete the work order. Specify the duration unit in the Duration Type field. Note Work order duration and work order line item duration are independent of each other. If you want work order duration to automatically show the sum of the work order line items’ duration, replace the Duration field on work orders with a custom roll-up summary field.

DurationType.title: Duration Type
DurationType.description: The unit of the duration: Minutes or Hours.

DurationInMinutes.title: Duration in Minutes
DurationInMinutes.description: The estimated duration in minutes. For internal use only.

ServiceAppointmentCount.title: Service Appointment Count
ServiceAppointmentCount.description: The number of service appointments on the work order.

StatusCategory.title: Status Category
StatusCategory.description: The category that each Status value falls into. The Status Category field has eight default values: seven values which are identical to the default Status values, and a None value for statuses without a status category.If you create custom Status values, you must indicate which category it belongs to. For example, if you create a Waiting for Response value, you may decide that it belongs in the On Hold category. To learn which processes reference StatusCategory, see How are Status Categories Used?

SuggestedMaintenanceDate.title: Suggested Maintenance Date
SuggestedMaintenanceDate.description: The suggested date that the work order is completed. When the work order is auto-generated from a maintenance plan, this field is automatically populated based on the maintenance plan’s settings.

MinimumCrewSize.title: Minimum Crew Size
MinimumCrewSize.description: The minimum crew size allowed for a crew assigned to the work order. If you’re not using the Field Service managed package, this field serves as a suggestion rather than a rule. If you are using the managed package, the scheduling optimizer counts the number of service crew members on a service crew to determine whether it fits a work order’s minimum crew size requirement.

RecommendedCrewSize.title: Recommended Crew Size
RecommendedCrewSize.description: The recommended number of people on the service crew assigned to the work order. For example, you might have a Minimum Crew Size of 2 and a Recommended Crew Size of 3.

IsGeneratedFromMaintenancePlan.title: Generated from maintenance plan
IsGeneratedFromMaintenancePlan.description: (Read Only) Indicates that the work order was generated from a maintenance plan (true), rather than manually created (false). Note This option is deselected for work orders that were generated from maintenance plans before Summer ’18.

ServiceReportLanguage.title: Service Report Language
ServiceReportLanguage.description: The language used for all service reports and service report previews created for the work order, its service appointments, and its work order line items and their service appointments. If the field is blank, service reports are generated in the default language in Salesforce of the person creating the report.To appear as an option in the ServiceReportLanguage field, a language must be set up in Translation Workbench or be one of Salesforce’s 18 fully supported languages. Rich text fields and service report section names aren’t translated.

ServiceDocumentTemplate.title: Service Document Template
ServiceDocumentTemplate.description: The template ID which sets the template for each service document for the Document Builder feature.
